author: Anonymous Beaker
title: Main starter
question: How do you know what (main ???) to use? I usually just keep guessing until it works, but that doesn’t seem very efficient.
student_answer:
You look at the @signature below (@htdf main) and put that datatype into (main ???).
For example, if it says:


(@htdf main)
(@signature ListOfBear -> ListOfBear)
I would run (main LOB1) if I defined it earlier, (main empty) if I want an empty state, or (main (cons ... ...)) if I want to be specific.
